Roundup (Oct. 10): Severn girls shut down St. Paul's in soccer, 4-0 Severn beats St. Paul's girls soccer 4-0 
Severn School simply had too much of too many things as the Admirals put away visiting St. Paul’s School for Girls, 4-0, Saturday. 
Four players scored for Severn, two in each half in the Maryland Interscholastic Athletic Association non-league game.

The Severn girls soccer team simply had too much of too many things as the Admirals put away visiting St. Paul's School for Girls, 4-0, on Saturday. 
Four players scored for Severn, two in each half, in the Interscholastic Athletic Association of Maryland nonleague game. 
Mackenzie Dixon scored on a cross from Danielle Drury to give the Admirals (3-8) a 3-0 cushion over the Gators (6-4). 
Football 
Archbishop Curley 35, Severn 13: Luke Nakich and Rodney Petitt Jr. had two touchdowns each to lead the Friars (3-2, 2-1 Maryland Interscholastic Athletic Association B Conference) past the host Admirals (3-4, 1-3).
